<div class="content_header">
	<h1>Add a Workout</h1>
</div>

<div class="content" id="select_device">
	<% if params[:device_type] %>
			<%= render :partial => 'form', :locals => { :submit_url => user_workouts_path(current_user) } %>
	<% else %>

<p>What type of device did you use to track this workout?</p>
	<ul>
	  <li><%= link_to 'Garmin', url_for(:action => 'new', :device_type => 'garmin'), :class => 'device_name' %> <span class="device_details">for example, the Forerunner 305, Forerunner 405...</span></li>
	  <li><%= link_to 'Polar', url_for(:action => 'new', :device_type => 'polar'), :class => 'device_name' %> <span class="device_details">for example, the RS400, RS800...</span></li>
	  <li><%= link_to 'Suunto', url_for(:action => 'new', :device_type => 'suunto'), :class => 'device_name' %> <span class="device_details">for example, the t6c...</span></li>
	  <li><%= link_to 'GPS', url_for(:action => 'new', :device_type => 'gpx'), :class => 'device_name' %> <span class="device_details">.gpx files from a cell phone or a GPS data logger designed for photography, sports, etc...</span></li>
	</ul>

	<p>If you don't see your device listed, <a href="http://zed9.uservoice.com" target="_new">suggest it and let the community vote!</a></p>

	<p>If you used multiple devices for this workout (e.g., a heart rate monitor and a GPS data logger), you will have a chance to merge the data when you upload the second file.</p>

	<% end -%>


</div>

